                            <comment id="13440685" author="raminder" created="Thu, 23 Aug 2012 21:25:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated the user profile page to work with entity id. Now its with work for openid users&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13441229" author="carlucci" created="Fri, 24 Aug 2012 15:01:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Raminder, I believe its a necessity in Rave for a Person Profile page to be accessible via a username.  Can you please revert the existing PersonController viewProfile function back, and create a second controller endpoint which can be accessible via the id?  That way it would serve both needs.  Perhaps /person/id/&lt;/p&gt;
{id}
&lt;p&gt; ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-1 on this commit&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13441257" author="raminder" created="Fri, 24 Aug 2012 15:33:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure i can do that. is there a function which is using PersonController viewProfile based on username?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13441260" author="carlucci" created="Fri, 24 Aug 2012 15:37:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No, but from a user perspective I think it is important to be able to access a profile page directly by knowing what a person&apos;s username is.  For example, in an environment were usernames are all standard, like &amp;lt;firstname&amp;gt;.&amp;lt;lastname&amp;gt;, I can easily get to someone&apos;s page by just knowing that pattern.  Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13441289" author="raminder" created="Fri, 24 Aug 2012 16:42:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;i made the changes and is fixed in rev 1376988&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
